A 43-year-old police Sergeant and two of his accomplices were arrested for stock theft and possession of suspected stolen cattle meat in Musina. Community members alerted cops about suspected stolen cattle meat being off-loaded in one of the houses at Mushenguville, a residential area on the outskirts of Musina. According to Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe on arrival, cops found a bakkie loaded with cattle meat parked inside the yard. He said the yard belongs to a police Sergeant from the Makhado Police Station. “The preliminary Police investigations revealed that the meat was of stolen stock and the three suspects were immediately arrested. “The pickup van still loaded with the meat was also seized,” Ngoepe said. The suspects will appear before the Musina Magistrate's Court soon. While the Provincial Commissioner of the South African Police Service in Limpopo Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba expressed disappointment in the involvement of cop in criminal activities. He warned Police members to stop engaging in any criminal activities as the law will equally be applied harshly regardless of their status.